title: Fathom - Killian's Tide 1-4 (2001) and Killian's Vessel (2007)
description:
English | CBR and CBZ | 5 Issues

Fathom: Killian's Tide #1-4
Publisher:  Aspen
Publication Date:  April - November 2001

Writers:  Michael Turner (#1-4), Bill O'Neil (#1-4), and Talent Caldwell (#1, 4)
Penciler:  Talent Caldwell
Inkers:  Jonathan Sibal (#1), Eric Basaldua (#1, 3), Jason Gorder (#1-4), Jay Leisten (#3), Marlo Alquiza (#3), and Matt Banning (#3), 
Colorists:  Justin Ponsor (#1), Ian Hannin (#1), Peter Steigerwald (#2-3), John Starr (#2-4), and Beth Sotelo (#2-3)
Letterers:  Robin Spehar and Dennis Heisler

The Killian's Tide mini series was published during Michael Turner's hiatus towards the end of the first Fathom volume.  Set before the events of that volume, it explores the back story of Killian and what drove him to act as he does.

Fathom: Killian's Vessel
Publisher:  Aspen
Publication Date:  July 2007

Writer:  Vince Hernandez
Penciler:  Ryan Odagawa
Colorist:  John Starr
Letterer:  Joshua Reed
Cover A:  Ryan Odagawa and John Starr
Cover B:  Michael Turner and Peter Steigerwald
Cover C:  Michael Turner and Peter Steigerwald

Killian's Vessel is a one-shot delving further into Killian's relationship with Anya and continuing from Fathom: Killian's Tide.

Thanks goes to Cooper and GreenGiant for this release.
